This paper is most likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it discusses the use of artificial immune systems for intrusion detection. It also mentions real-world intrusion problems, which further supports this categorization. 

The paper also involves the use of algorithms based on the latest immunological discoveries, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Additionally, the paper mentions the behaviour of Dendritic Cells, which are a type of immune cell, indicating that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as this sub-category deals with biologically-inspired computing. 

Finally, the paper discusses the use of immune-inspired algorithms, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) as this sub-category deals with the design and analysis of complex systems.
